  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently positioned just below the massive 6600 gamma wall (82B) and 11 points below the GEX flip at 6601, putting them in active buying mode to hedge short gamma as spot approaches these critical resistance levels. The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration at 6600-6610 creates a strong magnetic effect that should cap upside momentum and trigger dealer selling pressure on any push above 6601. \n\nWatch for mean reversion back toward the 6590 support wall, but if 6601 breaks decisively, expect accelerated dealer selling into the 6600-6605 zone where 130B in positive gamma will act as a concrete ceiling.",
